SIMPLE: refracted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refracted
<hw>Re*fract"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot. &
Zool.)</fld> <def>Bent backward angularly, as if half-broken; <as>as, a
<ex>refracted</ex> stem or leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Turned from a direct course by refraction; <as>as,
<ex>refracted</ex> rays of light</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refracting</ent>⟦br⟧
